it.polito.translator.symnet

Class RuleUnmarshallerS

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polito.translator.symnet.RuleUnmarshallerS

  • public class RuleUnmarshallerS
extends java.lang.Object
    Recursively scans all AST nodes of the input XML document.
    Depending on the type associated with the node,
    a different method is called and generates the corresponding rules in SEFL language.

    All methods with the name "generateType-" process the nested node information to generate a set of SEFL statements for the specific type.
    All the methods with the name "newName" produce a specific Name SEFL instruction.
    All the methods with the name "make..." produce a structure/element needed in a SEFL instruction.

    The starting point of the translation is on the generateRule () method and all the other methods are called recursively by it

    Version:
    1.0 01/07/2018
    Author:
    s211483

      • newib

        private org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.Expression newib(int index)
        The method newInstructionBlock is a recursive method to generate an Instruction Block SEFL rule for each table entry of the network function.
        The method generates a different set of instructions for the white list and for the black list.
        Example: InstructionBlock( If( Constrain(Tag("IP_SRC"), :==:(ConstantValue(ipToNumber(p(i)(0))))), InstructionBlock( If( Constrain(Tag("IPDst"), :==:(ConstantValue(ipToNumber(p(i)(1))))), Fail("Dropped"), NoOp)), NoOp ))
        Parameters:
        index - position of an element in the table of network function.
        Returns:
        If the index is a valid value, the method return an Invocation Method that represents a new instruction block for the element in the table of network function at the index position.
        Otherwise, If all the items in the table have been visited, the method returns a failed SEFL statement for the blacklist or an Assign SEFL statement for the whitelist.

      • newconstatvalue

        private org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.Expression newconstatvalue(java.lang.String str,
                                                            int index)
        Generate a new Method Invocation that represent a SEFL ConstantValue constructor for the input parameters.
        This method is inserted into a Constraint method that checks whether a field in the packet is equal to the value in the table of network functions. ConstantValue represents a value of the network function table. So we need to have the name of the field to be checked and the index of the table element. Example: ConstantValue(ipToNumber(p(i)(0))))
        Parameters:
        str - is the field of the packet to which you want to assign the constant value generated by the method.
        index - is an int value that represents the index of the element in the table.
        Returns:
        The ConstantValue Method Invocation generate.

        private org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.Expression newconcatlist()

        The concatenation of the rule and rules arrays is assigned to the variable rules.
